        <h2>Linear Collections</h2>
        <p align="justify">
            A Linear collection is a list of elements where one element follows the previous element. Elements in a linear
            collection are normally ordered by position, i.e. first, second, third etc.  grocery list is an example of this 
            type of collection.
        </p>
        <p align="justify">
            Linear collections can be either Direct access collections or Sequential access collections.
        </p>        
